Because my sister told you.

530
00:31:50,267 --> 00:31:52,200
In a way.

531
00:31:52,267 --> 00:31:54,434
She showed me severed arms and legs.

532
00:31:54,501 --> 00:31:55,666
I had no way to connect it,

533
00:31:55,733 --> 00:31:58,234
Except to her dolls and
what you had done to them.

534
00:31:58,300 --> 00:32:01,501
What I did to them.

535
00:32:01,566 --> 00:32:05,401
She tell you what I did to
her? Did she tell you that?

536
00:32:05,467 --> 00:32:07,666
I was so mean to her.

537
00:32:07,733 --> 00:32:11,067
She was such a stubborn tag-along.

538
00:32:11,134 --> 00:32:12,900
She was always getting into my stuff.

539
00:32:12,967 --> 00:32:14,401
Move!

540
00:32:14,467 --> 00:32:16,666
There were times when
I literally hated her.

541
00:32:16,733 --> 00:32:20,100
This one time, I was convinced
that she slit my tires.

542
00:32:20,167 --> 00:32:21,501
What is the matter with you?

543
00:32:21,566 --> 00:32:23,401
I didn't touch your stupid bike!

544
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:25,967
I didn't do it, I promise!

545
00:32:26,034 --> 00:32:28,067
So I went nuts on her dolls.

546
00:32:28,134 --> 00:32:31,700
Hiding them, hanging them.

547
00:32:31,767 --> 00:32:34,933
She'd run, tell my parents,

548
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:39,666
And write down in this little notepad of hers,
You know, about how she hated me right back.

549
00:32:39,733 --> 00:32:41,633
Writing those stupid
notes won't do anything.

550
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:44,034
Shut up and leave me alone.

551
00:32:47,933 --> 00:32:51,633
One day, I don't even know
what she did To bug me, really,

552
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:54,300
But I just chopped up all of her dolls.

553
00:33:10,100 --> 00:33:12,501
<i>Mom! Clay killed my dolls!</i>

554
00:33:14,067 --> 00:33:17,767
I got grounded for 2
weeks. I was home alone,

555
00:33:17,833 --> 00:33:20,100
Saw her latest entry.

556
00:33:20,167 --> 00:33:22,434
She'd torn out the page,
but I could see the imprint.

557
00:33:26,833 --> 00:33:29,200
She wrote, "i wish Clay's
arms and legs were cut off. "

558
00:33:32,566 --> 00:33:34,900
She wished for you the
same fate as her dolls.

559
00:33:34,967 --> 00:33:39,566
And when my parents were gone,

560
00:33:39,633 --> 00:33:41,434
I made that wish come true.

561
00:33:54,234 --> 00:33:58,566
Help me! Is this what you
wanted? what did you do to me?

562
00:34:00,467 --> 00:34:05,267
I tried to stop her before she
could call my parents or 911.

563
00:34:05,334 --> 00:34:08,367
I heard the screen door
to the kitchen slam.

564
00:34:08,434 --> 00:34:11,767
Gretchen, come back. it was just a joke.

565
00:34:11,833 --> 00:34:13,467
She was already gone.

566
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:19,666
She didn't come back that
night. Or the next, or the next.

567
00:34:21,467 --> 00:34:24,700
I don't know what I was thinking.

568
00:34:24,767 --> 00:34:28,067
She was 8 years old.

569
00:34:30,733 --> 00:34:35,100
I heard my mom sobbing every night.

570
00:34:35,167 --> 00:34:38,666
"how could this have happened?"

571
00:34:38,733 --> 00:34:41,200
I knew.

572
00:34:41,267 --> 00:34:44,367
But what I didn't know Was
what happened to Gretchen

573
00:34:44,434 --> 00:34:46,666
After I scared her away.

574
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:52,234
Do you?

575
00:34:53,234 --> 00:34:55,800
No.

576
00:34:55,867 --> 00:34:59,700
But I'll find out. I promise.

577
00:35:03,334 --> 00:35:05,967
I saw you talking to him.

578
00:35:06,034 --> 00:35:09,300
Gretchen, he didn't mean to hurt you.
He's been scared for you ever since.

579
00:35:09,367 --> 00:35:13,067
I've been in the dark, In the cold.

580
00:35:13,134 --> 00:35:15,034
All this time I was afraid to go home.

581
00:35:15,100 --> 00:35:16,967
Because you thought
your wish had come true?

582
00:35:17,034 --> 00:35:19,600
But he's fine. it was just a trick.

583
00:35:19,666 --> 00:35:21,900
- No, he's not fine.
- he's alive,

584
00:35:21,967 --> 00:35:23,600
And I'm dead and it's all his fault.

585
00:35:23,666 --> 00:35:26,700
He would give anything to take it back.

586
00:35:28,867 --> 00:35:32,167
There are no take backs
when it comes to the well.

587
00:35:32,234 --> 00:35:33,967
Ask your friend Sam.

588
00:35:59,734 --> 00:36:02,800
I don't get it. why is
the ghost going after Sam?

589
00:36:03,066 --> 00:36:05,200
I thought she was mad at her brother.

590
00:36:05,267 --> 00:36:07,066
I'm dealing with
an angry 8-year-old

591
00:36:07,133 --> 00:36:09,233
Who keeps changing
the rules as she goes.

592
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:11,467
None of it explains how
she got down the well.

593
00:36:11,534 --> 00:36:12,867
She wrote a note

594
00:36:12,933 --> 00:36:15,901
Asking for the well's help
in punishing her brother.

595
00:36:15,966 --> 00:36:18,567
That's how this all
started. but then, Eli and i

596
00:36:18,634 --> 00:36:22,567
Found this With her
dolls at the old house.

597
00:36:23,767 --> 00:36:26,901
"i wish he could know she was here. "

598
00:36:26,966 --> 00:36:28,933
- Did her brother write this?
- no, I don't think so.

599
00:36:30,667 --> 00:36:32,667
Where are those tiles that Sam brought?

600
00:36:32,734 --> 00:36:35,534
I put them over here. I
wasn't sure if you were serious

601
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:38,700
About selling it as a garden fixture.

602
00:36:38,767 --> 00:36:41,966
What do the tiles have
to do with any of this?

603
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:44,901
This is how I'm gonna get
Gretchen to tell me the truth.

604
00:36:56,467 --> 00:37:00,734
"make a wish of your very own.
"hide it deep within the stone".

605
00:37:00,750 --> 00:37:03,066
Gretchen, you thought
the well had real powers

606
00:37:03,133 --> 00:37:04,867
And that's how your brother got hurt.

607
00:37:06,267 --> 00:37:07,667
Can I speak to her?

608
00:37:07,734 --> 00:37:11,300
She's here. she's angry.

609
00:37:11,367 --> 00:37:14,467
Like she was the time that she
made a wish Wanting to hurt you.

610
00:37:16,167 --> 00:37:17,834
Hide it deep within the stone.

611
00:37:17,901 --> 00:37:19,767
Is it still in the stone?

612
00:37:19,834 --> 00:37:21,700
I watched it fall away over time.

613
00:37:21,767 --> 00:37:24,600
Years and years I was down there.

614
00:37:24,667 --> 00:37:26,200
Because of you.

615
00:37:26,267 --> 00:37:29,734
Look, whatever she's saying,
Please just tell her I'm sorry.

616
00:37:29,801 --> 00:37:32,200
She's sorry, too.

617
00:37:32,267 --> 00:37:35,567
Even if she doesn't
remember feeling that way.

618
00:37:35,634 --> 00:37:36,700
When you thought your wish had come true

619
00:37:36,767 --> 00:37:40,400
And you saw your brother
bleeding, Maybe even dying...

620
00:37:40,467 --> 00:37:43,267
You came here to take
back your wish, didn't you?

621
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:47,202
It was so hard to reach.

622
00:38:01,434 --> 00:38:04,700
You said there were no
takebacks. You're right.

623
00:38:04,767 --> 00:38:07,300
Even though you want to,

624
00:38:07,367 --> 00:38:09,834
